goals.rationale: This visualization will show the distribution of life expectancy across different countries and if there are any outliers or differences between clusters.

goals.question: Is there a correlation between fertility rate and life expectancy?

goals.rationale: This visualization will show if there is a relationship between the number of children born to a woman and the average life expectancy of a country's population.

goals.visualization: bar chart of cluster vs. count
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the number of countries in each cluster and if there are any clusters that are over or underrepresented.

goals.question: How has the average fertility rate changed over time?
goals.visualization: line chart of year vs. fertility

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data_grouped = data.groupby('year')['pop'].sum().reset_index()
    
    plt.plot(data_grouped['year'], data_grouped['pop'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the trend of population over time?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    box_plot = data.boxplot(column='life_expect', by='country', grid=False, rot=90)
    plt.title("How does life expectancy vary across different countries?")
    plt.suptitle("")
    plt.xlabel("Country")
    plt.ylabel("Life Expectancy")
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        box_plot.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    avg_fertility = data.groupby('year')['fertility'].mean()
    avg_fertility.plot(kind='line')
    
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average Fertility Rate')
    plt.title('How has the average fertility rate changed over time?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
